---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How to Get Your Shopify Collaborator Code | Travis Smith"
  description="A quick step-by-step guide to generating a Shopify collaborator request code so your consultant can access your store without using a staff user seat."
>
  <Navigation />

  <main class="collab">
    <div class="container container--narrow">

      <header class="collab__header">
        <span class="label">Resource</span>
        <h1 class="collab__title">How to Get Your Shopify Collaborator Code</h1>
        <p class="collab__subtitle">
          This takes about two minutes. You'll generate a 4-digit code in your Shopify admin and send it to me — then I request access and you approve it. That's it.
        </p>
        <p class="collab__byline">By Travis Smith — former Head of Design at Shopify, 2020–2025</p>
      </header>

      <!-- What it is -->
      <section class="collab__section">
        <h2 class="collab__section-title">What collaborator access is</h2>
        <p class="collab__body">
          Shopify's Collaborator Access lets a Shopify Partner (like a consultant or agency) into your store without taking up one of your staff user seats. You control exactly which sections of the store they can see, and you can revoke access at any time — instantly, from your admin.
        </p>
        <p class="collab__body">
          It's the standard, safe way for consultants to work inside a client's store. Shopify built it specifically for this purpose.
        </p>
        <div class="collab__callout">
          <p><strong>It doesn't count against your staff user limit</strong> — collaborator accounts are separate from staff accounts, so adding me doesn't use a seat you'd otherwise pay for.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Steps -->
      <section class="collab__section">
        <h2 class="collab__section-title">How to generate your code</h2>

        <ol class="collab__steps">

          <li class="collab__step">
            <div class="collab__step-num">01</div>
            <div class="collab__step-body">
              <h3 class="collab__step-title">Log into your Shopify admin</h3>
              <p>Go to <strong>your-store.myshopify.com/admin</strong> — or just open your store admin the way you normally would.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="collab__step">
            <div class="collab__step-num">02</div>
            <div class="collab__step-body">
              <h3 class="collab__step-title">Go to Settings → Users</h3>
              <p>In the bottom-left of your admin, click <strong>Settings</strong>. Then click <strong>Users</strong> from the left-hand menu.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="collab__step">
            <div class="collab__step-num">03</div>
            <div class="collab__step-body">
              <h3 class="collab__step-title">Find the Collaborators section</h3>
              <p>Scroll down the Users page until you see the <strong>Collaborators</strong> section. You may need to scroll past your current staff members.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="collab__step">
            <div class="collab__step-num">04</div>
            <div class="collab__step-body">
              <h3 class="collab__step-title">Click "Get collaborator request code"</h3>
              <p>You'll see a button or link that says <strong>"Get collaborator request code"</strong>. Click it. Shopify will generate a 4-digit code.</p>
              <p class="collab__step-note">If you don't see this option, make sure you're the store owner or have the "Manage users" permission.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="collab__step">
            <div class="collab__step-num">05</div>
            <div class="collab__step-body">
              <h3 class="collab__step-title">Send me the 4-digit code</h3>
              <p>Reply to my email with the code. It's just four digits — something like <strong>7343</strong>. That's all I need.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- What happens next -->
      <section class="collab__section">
        <h2 class="collab__section-title">What happens after you send the code</h2>
        <p class="collab__body">
          I'll enter your store URL and the 4-digit code in my Shopify Partner Dashboard and submit a collaborator request. You'll get a notification in your Shopify admin to approve the request — it'll show you exactly which sections of the store I'm requesting access to.
        </p>
        <p class="collab__body">
          Once you approve it, I can access your store. I'll show up in your Collaborators list, not your Staff list. You can see exactly what I'm doing, and you can remove access at any time from the same Users page.
        </p>
        <div class="collab__callout collab__callout--tip">
          <p><strong>Tip:</strong> When you approve, I recommend granting full access. I need to see your Analytics, Marketing, Products, and Orders sections to give you accurate recommendations. You can always narrow it down if you prefer.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="collab__section">
        <h2 class="collab__section-title">Common questions</h2>

        <dl class="collab__faq">
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>Does it cost anything to give collaborator access?</dt>
            <dd>No. Collaborator accounts are free and don't use a staff user seat regardless of your Shopify plan.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>Can I revoke access at any time?</dt>
            <dd>Yes, immediately. Go to Settings → Users → Collaborators, find my name, and click Remove. Access is gone instantly.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>What will you be able to see?</dt>
            <dd>Only what you approve during the access request — typically: Products, Orders, Customers, Analytics, Marketing, and Online Store. I won't have access to your billing, payment settings, or account settings unless you specifically approve those.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>Does the 4-digit code expire?</dt>
            <dd>Yes — the code expires after a short window (usually a few hours). If it expires before I use it, just generate a new one the same way and send it over.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>Will my collaborator access expire automatically?</dt>
            <dd>Yes — if I don't log into your store for 90 days, Shopify automatically removes collaborator access. This is a built-in safety feature.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="collab__faq-item">
            <dt>I can't find the Collaborators section. What's wrong?</dt>
            <dd>A few possibilities: you may not have permission to manage users (only the store owner or admins with that permission can generate codes), or you may be on a very old Shopify plan. If you're stuck, email me and we'll figure it out together.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <section class="collab__cta">
        <h2>Questions? Just email me.</h2>
        <p>If you run into any trouble generating the code or approving access, reply to my email or reach out directly. Takes 30 seconds to sort out.</p>
        <Button href="mailto:hello@fully-operational.com" variant="secondary">hello@fully-operational.com</Button>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .collab {
    padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-12));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-20);
  }

  .collab__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .collab__header .label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .collab__title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, var(--text-4xl));
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .collab__subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .collab__byline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .collab__section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .collab__section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .collab__section-title {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .collab__body {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .collab__body:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .collab__callout {
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .collab__callout p { margin: 0; }

  /* Steps */
  .collab__steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .collab__step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .collab__step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 4px;
    min-width: 24px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .collab__step-body {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .collab__step-title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .collab__step-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0;
  }

  .collab__step-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .collab__step-note {
    font-size: var(--text-sm) !important;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .collab__faq {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .collab__faq-item {
    padding: var(--space-6) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .collab__faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .collab__faq-item dt {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .collab__faq-item dd {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .collab__cta {
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-10);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .collab__cta h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .collab__cta p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 480px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .collab__cta {
      padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
    }
  }
</style>
